cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.GT, cs.RO

This paper discusses the evaluation of Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) algorithms on Atari games, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a standardized benchmark for evaluating DRL algorithms, which is related to the sub-category of optimization and learning (cs.LG). The use of Atari games as a benchmark involves computer vision (cs.CV) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the reproducibility of results, which is related to robotics (cs.RO).
